'''Benson James Boone''' (born June 25, 2002) is an American singer-songwriter. Born and raised in [[Monroe, Washington]], he began his music career when he filled in for a friend at a talent show. Boone later appeared on ''[[American Idol]]'', where he briefly competed before withdrawing voluntarily. He continued to gain popularity on TikTok and subsequently signed a contract with Night Street Records, the music label owned by [[Imagine Dragons]] frontman [[Dan Reynolds]].

Boone's debut single, "[[Ghost Town (Benson Boone song)|Ghost Town]]", was released in October 2021 and charted in 16 countries. Boone has since released multiple successful singles, including "[[In the Stars (Benson Boone song)|In the Stars]]" (April 2022) and "[[Beautiful Things (Benson Boone song)|Beautiful Things]]" (January 2024), the latter topping the charts in the United Kingdom, Australia, Canada, France, Germany, Ireland and New Zealand.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/benson-boone-beautiful-things-number-1-song/ | title=Benson Boone celebrates first UK Number 1 single with Beautiful Things | website=[[Official Charts Company|Official Charts]] | access-date=March 24, 2024 | archive-date=March 22, 2024 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240322174520/https://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/benson-boone-beautiful-things-number-1-song/ | url-status=live }}</ref> It also became his first song to enter the top five on the U.S.  [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]], reaching number two.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Unterberger |first=Andrew |date=2024-02-14 |title=Benson Boone on the Relationship That 'Terrified' Him Into Writing Smash Hit 'Beautiful Things' |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/rock/benson-boone-beautiful-things-inspiration-tour-1235607010/ |access-date=2024-02-15 |magazine=Billboard |language=en-US |archive-date=May 2, 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240502152232/https://www.billboard.com/music/rock/benson-boone-beautiful-things-inspiration-tour-1235607010/ |url-status=live }}</ref> His debut studio album, ''[[Fireworks & Rollerblades]]'', was released on April 5, 2024.

==Early life==
Boone was born in [[Monroe, Washington]], to Kerry and Nate Boone.<ref name=":0">{{cite web|last1=Berg|first1=Jake|title= Local teen sings his way onto TV’s “American Idol” |url= https://www.snoho.com/news/2021/feb/10/local-teen-sings-his-way-onto-tvs-american-idol/ |website=Snohomish Tribune |access-date=November 9, 2024|date=February 10, 2021}}</ref> Boone grew up with four sisters, Kaylee, Natalee, Emma, and Claire.<ref name="Karlinsky 2021">{{cite web|last1=Karlinsky|first1=Malia|title=Benson Boone from Monroe, WA sings his way onto 'American Idol' premiere|url=https://komonews.com/news/entertainment/benson-boone-america-idol-katy-perry-abc|website=Komo News|access-date=March 20, 2022|date=February 11, 2021|archive-date=February 12, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210212002713/https://komonews.com/news/entertainment/benson-boone-america-idol-katy-perry-abc|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Boone|first1=Kerry|title= Kerry Boone is fundraising for Take The Next Step|url= https://www.justgiving.com/fundraising/boonebread2019|website= JustGiving|access-date=January 4, 2025|date=December 3, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Fynn|first1=Jessica|title=Benson Boone|url=https://boysbygirls.co.uk/conversations/benson-boone |website=Boys By Girls |access-date=March 20, 2022|date=January 24, 2022}}</ref> He attended [[Monroe High School (Washington)|Monroe High School]] and was a member of the school's competitive [[diving (sport)|diving]] team.<ref name="Brown 2021">{{cite web |last1=Brown |first1=And

