'''Shakira Isabel Mebarak Ripoll'''{{Family name footnote|[[Mebarak]]|Ripoll|lang=Spanish}} ({{IPAc-en|ʃ|ə|ˈ|k|iːr|ə}} {{respell|shə|KEER|ə}}, {{IPA|es|ʃaˈkiɾa isaˈβel meβaˈɾak riˈpol|lang}}; born 2 February 1977)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.biography.com/people/shakira-189151|title=Shakira: Singer (1977–)|work=Biography|access-date=28 March 2013|archive-date=26 March 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130326013249/http://www.biography.com/people/shakira-189151|url-status=bot: unknown}}</ref> is a Colombian singer-songwriter. Referred to as the "[[Honorific nicknames in popular music|Queen of Latin Music]]", she has had a [[Cultural impact of Shakira|significant impact]] on the musical landscape of [[Latin America]] and has been credited with popularizing [[Hispanophone]] music on a global level.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2022-06-07 |title=Así ha cambiado Shakira: Desde 'Pies descalzos' hasta su ruptura con Gerard Piqué |url=https://www.lavanguardia.com/gente/20220607/8319307/asi-cambiado-shakira-pies-descalzos-ruptura-gerard-pique-asc-gnt.html |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231130075407/https://www.lavanguardia.com/gente/20220607/8319307/asi-cambiado-shakira-pies-descalzos-ruptura-gerard-pique-asc-gnt.html |archive-date=30 November 2023 |access-date=2022-06-09 |website=La Vanguardia |language=es}}</ref> The recipient of [[List of awards and nominations received by Shakira|various accolades]], she has won four [[Grammy Awards]] and fifteen [[Latin Grammy Awards]], including three [[Latin Grammy Award for Song of the Year|Song of the Year]] wins.

Born and raised in [[Barranquilla]], Shakira made her recording debut with [[Sony Music|Sony Music Colombia]] at the age of 14. Following the commercial failure of her first two albums, ''[[Magia (Shakira album)|Magia]]'' (1991) and ''[[Peligro (Shakira album)|Peligro]]'' (1993), she rose to prominence with the next two, ''[[Pies Descalzos]]'' (1995) and ''[[Dónde Están los Ladrones?]]'' (1998). Shakira entered the English-language market with her fifth album, ''[[Laundry Service (album)|Laundry Service]]'' (2001), which sold over 13 million copies worldwide, becoming the best-selling album of all time by a female Latin artist. Her success was further solidified with the Spanish-language albums ''[[Fijación Oral, Vol. 1]]'' (2005), ''[[Sale el Sol]]'' (2010), ''[[El Dorado (Shakira album)|El Dorado]]'' (2017), and ''[[Las Mujeres Ya No Lloran]]'' (2024), all of which topped the [[Billboard Top Latin Albums|''Billboard'' Top Latin Albums]] chart, making her the first woman with number-one albums across four different decades. Her English-language albums ''[[Oral Fixation, Vol. 2

