'''Kendrick Lamar Duckworth''' (born June 17, 1987) is an American rapper. Regarded as one of the most influential [[hip-hop]] artists of his generation, and [[Billboard and Vibe's 50 Greatest Rappers of All Time|one of the greatest rappers of all time]], he is known for his technical artistry and complex songwriting. He was awarded the 2018 [[Pulitzer Prize for Music]], becoming the first musician outside of the [[Classical music|classical]] and [[jazz]] genres to receive the honor.

Lamar began releasing music under the [[stage name]] '''K.Dot''' while he was attending high school. He signed with [[Top Dawg Entertainment]] (TDE) in 2005, where he co-founded the hip hop [[Supergroup (music)|supergroup]] [[Black Hippy]]. Following the success of his [[Alternative hip hop|alternative rap]] debut album ''[[Section.80]]'' (2011), Lamar secured a joint contract with [[Dr. Dre]]'s [[Aftermath Entertainment]] and [[Interscope Records]]. He rose to prominence with his [[gangsta rap]]-influenced second album ''[[Good Kid, M.A.A.D City]]'' (2012), which became the [[Billboard 200#Most weeks on the chart|longest-charting hip hop studio album]] in the [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]]'s chart history; ''[[Rolling Stone]]'' named it the greatest [[concept album]] of all time. Lamar's third album, ''[[To Pimp a Butterfly]]'' (2015), infused hip-hop with historical [[African-American music]] genres such as [[jazz]], [[funk]], and [[soul music|soul]]. It became his first of five consecutive number-one albums on the [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]] chart, and was one of the most critically acclaimed albums of the [[2010s in music|2010s]].

In 2015, Lamar garnered his first number-one song on the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]], after featuring on the remix of [[Taylor Swift]]'s "[[Bad Blood (Taylor Swift song)|Bad Blood]]". His critical and commercial success continued with his [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]] and [[Pop music|pop]]-leaning fourth album ''[[Damn (album)|Damn]]'' (2017), yielding his second Hot 100 number-one single, "[[Humble (song)|Humble]]". He curated original songs for the [[Black Panther: The Album|soundtrack album]] of the 2018 film ''[[Black Panther (film)|Black Panther]]'', earning a nomination for the [[Academy Award for Best Original Song]] for the US and UK top-ten single "[[All the Stars]]" (with [[SZA]]). Lama

