'''Koo Jun-yup''' ({{Korean|hangul=구준엽|rr=Gu Junyeop}}; born September 11, 1969), also known by his stage name '''DJ Koo''', is a South Korean singer, DJ, music producer, dancer, and songwriter. He is well-known as a member of the legendary [[K-pop]] duo [[Clon (duo)|CLON]]. Koo is one of the first-generation [[Hallyu]] stars when CLON gained huge popularity internationally, most notably in [[Taiwan]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=The Seeds of Hallyu |url=https://thediplomat.com/2010/10/the-seeds-of-hallyu/ |access-date=2022-04-24 |website=thediplomat.com |language=en-US}}</ref> He is also known as one of South Korea's most renowned DJs, who has performed at the [[Ultra Music Festival]], [[Ultra Korea]], and [[Seoul World DJ Festival|World DJ Festival]].

==Early life==
Koo was born and raised in [[Seoul]], South Korea. He has an older sister Koo Eun-yeong ({{Korean|hangul=구은영|hanja=具恩英|labels=no}}).<ref>{{Cite web |script-title=ko:손혜림 기문둔갑 02)3476-3433|url=https://blog.naver.com/sonherim/222307209210 |access-date=2022-07-23 |website=[[Naver Blog]]}}</ref>{{Unreliable source?|date=March 2024|reason=Self-published blog}} His parents divorced when he was eleven years old. He went to Seoul Sinjung Elementary School and Seocho Middle School. Koo attended [[Kyunggi High School]], where he met fellow [[Clon (duo)|CLON]] member Kang Won-rae. Koo graduated from [[Kyungnam University]] with a bachelor's degree in Industrial Design.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2015-11-08 |script-title=ko:[궁금타] 경남 출신 연예인 누구누구I(창원) |url=http://m.knnews.co.kr/mView.php?idxno=1163327 |access-date=2022-06-19 |website=[[Kyongnam Shinmun]] |language=ko}}</ref>

== Career ==
=== Career beginnings ===
In 1990, Koo and his best friend from [[Kyunggi High School]] Kang Won-rae joined a dancing competition, which they won fourth and first place respectively. Koo and Kang were signed by [[Lee Soo-man]], founder of [[SM Entertainment]], as backup dancers for singer [[Hyun Jin-young]] and formed a group called [[Hyun Jin-young#Hyun Jin-young and Wawa|Hyun Jin-young and Wawa]]. In 1991, Koo enlisted for his two-year [[Conscription in South Korea|mandatory military service]] and began to serve in the army. After completing his military service, he and singer Lee Tak briefly formed a group called Tak and Jun in 1993 and released their single titled "Hunch".

=== 1996–2002: CLON ===
In 1996, Koo and Kang Won-rae were signed by Media Line Entertainment and debuted as [[Clon (duo)|CLON]]. Their first album ''Are You Ready?'' (1996), featured the hit song "Kungtari Shabara", sold over 1.12 million copies in South Korea.<ref>{{Cite web  |date=2020-07-25 |script-title=ko:'런닝맨' 박준형-김건모-DJ DOC, 90년대 레전드의 음반판매량은? |url=https://www.chosun.com/site/data/html_dir/2015/08/17/2015081700858.html |access-date=2022-04-27 |website=[[The Chosun Ilbo]] |language=ko}}</ref>

In 1998, CLON signed with [[Rock Records]] and released the Taiwanese version of ''One More Time,'' which was a compilation of hit songs from Clon's first album ''Are You Ready?'' (1996) and second album ''One More Time'' (1997).<ref name=":7">{{Cite web |date=1999-02-24 |script-title=ko:클론 ,『쿠롱 띵하오』대만을 뒤흔들다 |url=https://www.donga.com/news/amp/all/19990224/7421914/1 |access-date=2022-06-10 |website=[[The Dong-A Ilbo]]}}</ref> Koo took the title of "Taiwan's Sexiest Man" in 1998 and 1999.<ref name=":6">{{Cite web |date=2017-07-01 |script-title=ko:[종합] '불후' 전설 클론의 메가 히트곡 퍼레이드 |url=https://m.mk.co.kr/

